Merge pull request #16 from mckellardw/master

- Code clean-up and README updates for `from_STARsolo`

Merge pull request #15 from mckellardw/from_STARsolo

from_starsolo
- Removed `from_multi_cellranger` b/c it isn't ready yet and need to merge `from_STARsolo`; will add back as a separate branch
- Fixed core usage for `generate_refFlat_script_both.R` so it is actually controlled by snakemake

-Switched TagReadWithGeneFunction with featureCounts for parallelization speed-up 
-umi_tools will replace other DropSeqUtils tool, but doesn't quite work 
yet

-Finally solved the chromosome sort order issue using a temporary genome file (made from the input bed file for `bedtools coverage`)
-Also dropped the new "SingleCellHMM_MW.bash" and cleaned up R scripts 
into from_cellranger

-Added `-g` flag to `bedtools coverage` to further attempt prevention of sort issues
-Additional R script clean up

-Added '--nonamecheck' to the bedtools coverage call in SingleCellHMM_MW.sh; prevents issues from sorting/chromosome naming conventions (fixes bug where not all chroms have TARs labeled)
-Added 'quietly' for lib loading in R scripts
-Fixed bug where some chromosomes are left out of TAR annotations

-Fixed read tagging bug which prevented TAR count matrices from being generated
-Cleaned up R scripts a bit

-Added some messages in analyzeExpressionMat.R for QC/etc.
-Fixed some STARsolo-specific file naming bugs

-Renamed input/output files to match STARsolo formats
-Changed naming scheme for HMM output refFlat annotations

-Moving bamtobed conversion to an earlier rule
-gzip-ing tmp bed files becase disk space requirements will be crazy for 
large jobs if I don't (~5-7gb per sample, just for these .bed files)

added Snakefile and config.yaml

Added Snakefile and confi.yaml files that will take fastq files and generate 3 expression matrices.
1. Gene expression matrix.
2. HMM expression matrix (labelled with in and out) without considering direction.
3. HMM expression matrix (labelled with in and out) considering direction.
